        public abstract List<String> getKeys(org.testng.ITestResult result)
        Return the keys the result should be associated with. For instance, for a view where the result should be ordered by package, it should return the package name. It returns null is the result do not belong to any group, for instance if you want a failedByPackage view, and the test is not failed. It returns a list and not unique value in case the splitting is not unique. For package, class etc, the test will only have 1 key, but if you're working with groups for instance, you can have one tests tagged with both SYI and seller reg and buyer reg.
